<div class="container">
<div class="section"><div class="section-title"><span class="sec-num">01</span> Executive Summary</div><p class="body-text">Thus SpokeThe Gentlemen [70 IOC(s) | 24 TTP(s) | Source: Check Point Research]</p><div class="meta-grid" style="margin-top:18px;"><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">CVE / Advisory ID</span><span class="meta-value"><span class="mono">N/A</span></span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Severity</span><span class="meta-value"><span class="badge sev-critical">CRITICAL</span></span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Risk Score</span><span class="meta-value"><span style="color:#dc2626;font-weight:700;font-family:var(--font-mono);">10.0 / 10</span></span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Vulnerability Class</span><span class="meta-value">Remote Code Execution (CWE-78 / CWE-94)</span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Threat Actor</span><span class="meta-value"><span class="mono">CDB-IR-02</span></span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">TLP Classification</span><span class="meta-value"><span class="badge badge-tlp">TLP:RED</span></span></div></div><div style="margin-top:12px;"><a href="https://research.checkpoint.com/2026/thus-spoke-the-gentlemen/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="src-link">Source Article &#8599;</a></div></div>
<div class="section"><div class="section-title"><span class="sec-num">02</span> Vulnerability Intelligence</div><div class="score-grid"><div class="score-card"><div class="score-big" style="color:#dc2626;">N/A</div><div class="score-label">CVSS 3.1 Score</div></div><div class="score-card"><div class="score-big" style="color:#f59e0b;">94.1%</div><div class="score-label">EPSS 30-day probability</div></div><div class="score-card"><div class="score-big" style="color:#ef4444;">YES</div><div class="score-label">CISA KEV Listed</div></div><div class="score-card"><div class="score-big" style="color:var(--accent);">10.0</div><div class="score-label">Composite Risk /10</div><div class="risk-bar-wrap"><div class="risk-bar" style="width:100.0%;background:#dc2626;"></div></div></div></div></div>
<div class="section"><div class="section-title"><span class="sec-num">03</span> Affected Products &amp; Versions</div><p class="muted-text">Refer to vendor advisory for complete affected product list. CVE: N/A</p></div>
<div class="section"><div class="section-title"><span class="sec-num">04</span> Threat Context &amp; Attack Surface</div><p class="body-text">Remote code execution grants attackers the ability to execute arbitrary operating system commands in the context of the application server process, typically resulting in full server compromise, lateral movement, and persistent backdoor installation.</p><div class="meta-grid" style="margin-top:16px;"><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Attack Vector</span><span class="meta-value">Network</span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Attack Complexity</span><span class="meta-value">Low</span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Privileges Required</span><span class="meta-value">None</span></div><div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">User Interaction</span><span class="meta-value">None</span></div></div></div>
<div class="section"><div class="section-title"><span class="sec-num">05</span> MITRE ATT&amp;CK v15 Mapping</div><div class="attack-grid"><div class="attack-card"><div class="attack-id" style="color:#6b7280;">T1595</div><div class="attack-name">Active Scanning</div><div class="attack-tactic">Reconnaissance</div></div><div class="attack-card"><div class="attack-id" style="color:#6b7280;">T1593</div><div class="attack-name">Search Open Websites/Domains</div><div class="attack-tactic">Reconnaissance</div></div><div class="attack-card"><div class="attack-id" style="color:#dc2626;">T1566</div><div class="attack-name">Phishing</div><div class="attack-tactic">Initial Access</div></div><div class="attack-card"><div class="attack-id" style="color:#dc2626;">T1190</div><div class="attack-name">Exploit Public-Facing Application</div><div class="attack-tactic">Initial Access</div></div><div class="attack-card"><div class="attack-id" style="color:#ea580c;">T1078</div><div class="attack-name">Valid Accounts</div><div class="attack-tactic">Defense Evasion / Persistence</div></div></div></div>
<div class="section"><div class="section-title"><span class="sec-num">06</span> Technical Analysis</div><div class="code-wrap"><span class="code-lang">Analysis</span><pre class="code-block">VULNERABILITY ROOT CAUSE
User-controlled input is passed unsanitized to OS-level command execution
functions (exec, system, subprocess with shell=True).

ATTACK VECTOR:
  HTTP request parameters containing shell metacharacters (; | $(...) backticks)
  that the application passes to an OS command interpreter.

POST-EXPLOITATION CHAIN:
  1. RCE payload establishes reverse shell or drops webshell
  2. Attacker reads environment variables (API keys, DB credentials, secrets)
  3. Internal network pivot via compromised server as jump host
  4. Persistence via cron job or systemd service modification</pre></div></div>
